data.name: Insane Generate All Divisors
data.description:
Note: only Python 3.6 is available in this kata.

---

This is the insane version of [Find the divisors!](https://www.codewars.com/kata/544aed4c4a30184e960010f4).

---

Given a positive integer `n >= 2`, your function `divisors` should return all its divisors.

Note that for simplicity, you should return a *set* of all the divisors of `n` in this kata. Moreover, `1` and `n` are not excluded from the results.

---

Test details:

- Small numbers: `200` tests, `10 <= n < 10^4`
- Medium numbers: `150` tests, `10^4 <= n < 10^9`
- Big numbers: `100` tests, `10^9 <= n < 10^13`
- Insane numbers: `40` tests, `10^13 <= n < 10^15`
